---run: false---
## Downloads Organiser

Automatically sorts the Downloads folder into categorised subdirectories.

Safe to run regularly — it will not overwrite existing organised files.
---

---run: true---
Look at the Downloads folder and list all the files. Group them mentally by type:
- Documents: .pdf, .doc, .docx, .txt, .md
- Spreadsheets: .xlsx, .csv, .numbers
- Images: .png, .jpg, .jpeg, .gif, .webp, .heic
- Archives: .zip, .tar, .gz, .7z
- Code: .js, .py, .rs, .ts, .html, .css
- Everything else: Miscellaneous
---

---run: true---
Create the following folders inside Downloads if they do not already exist:
Documents, Spreadsheets, Images, Archives, Code, Miscellaneous
---

---run: true---
Move each file from Downloads into the appropriate subfolder based on its extension.
Do not move files that are already inside a subfolder.
After moving, list the contents of each subfolder so I can verify everything looks correct.
---

---run: false---
## Customisation tips

Add or change extensions by editing the groupings in the first run cell.
You can also change the destination folder names to suit your workflow.
---
